    {
      "text": "What is the appropriate approach to treat a child who is attending school and has a repeated occurrence of infections in the upper respiratory tract, difficulty in breathing through the nose, and hearing problems, along with the observation of a palate that is significantly raised in shape?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Tonsillectomy"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Adenoidectomy"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Adenoidectomy with grommet insertion"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Myringotomy with grommet insertion"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: C) <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4606b784281692777180cad55735b5\">Adenoidectomy</span> with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"efcdc8d2f71692777188341ac61941\">grommet</span> insertion</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Adenoidectomy with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"efcdc8d2f71692777188341ac61941\">grommet</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c88a7c1a0116927771909b2463968d\">insertion</span> </strong>is the preferred approach for a child presenting with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c64e3a661b1692777197afc2ff7bca\">recurrent</span> upper <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cfad80a0f716927771979aae100f95\">respiratory</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1a1307223f16927772017a994bfc39\">tract</span> infections, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31c5d0e75f16927771938d8e2daa4c\">nasal</span> breathing difficulty, hearing problems, and a high-arched palate. These symptoms suggest <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"11fd4461491692777180591f35947b\">adenoid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3baac9012a1692777189cb4dc70c04\">hypertrophy</span> causing upper <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3b9dd3166f1692777180b697887ccb\">airway</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"39f44b27bf169277719416f29a74ee\">obstruction</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"22053f7eef1692777187c1142bad20\">Eustachian</span> tube dysfunction, leading to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b913f965781692777194c867946afe\">otitis</span> media with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"73909075e71692777187f08d3c9b7e\">effusion</span> (OME).\n\n\t<ul>\n\t\t<li><strong>Adenoidectomy</strong> relieves <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31c5d0e75f16927771938d8e2daa4c\">nasal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"39f44b27bf169277719416f29a74ee\">obstruction</span> and reduces <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c64e3a661b1692777197afc2ff7bca\">recurrent</span> infections.</li>\n\t\t<li><strong>Grommet insertion</strong> helps in draining <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7879d301d169277719255fe8818dc\">middle ear</span> fluid, improving hearing.</li>\n\t</ul>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Tonsillectomy (Option A)</strong>: <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"68899ab3a11692777200d8823b50d8\">Tonsillectomy</span> alone is not indicated as the child primarily has symptoms related to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"11fd4461491692777180591f35947b\">adenoid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3baac9012a1692777189cb4dc70c04\">hypertrophy</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"22053f7eef1692777187c1142bad20\">Eustachian</span> tube dysfunction, not <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c64e3a661b1692777197afc2ff7bca\">recurrent</span> tonsillitis.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Adenoidectomy (Option B)</strong>: While <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4606b784281692777180cad55735b5\">adenoidectomy</span> addresses the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31c5d0e75f16927771938d8e2daa4c\">nasal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"39f44b27bf169277719416f29a74ee\">obstruction</span> and infections, it does not directly manage the hearing problems caused by OME. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"efcdc8d2f71692777188341ac61941\">Grommet</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c88a7c1a0116927771909b2463968d\">insertion</span> is essential for addressing <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7879d301d169277719255fe8818dc\">middle ear</span> fluid.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Myringotomy with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"efcdc8d2f71692777188341ac61941\">grommet</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c88a7c1a0116927771909b2463968d\">insertion</span> (Option D)</strong>: While this resolves <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d7879d301d169277719255fe8818dc\">middle ear</span> fluid, it does not address the underlying issue of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"11fd4461491692777180591f35947b\">adenoid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3baac9012a1692777189cb4dc70c04\">hypertrophy</span> causing <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31c5d0e75f16927771938d8e2daa4c\">nasal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"39f44b27bf169277719416f29a74ee\">obstruction</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c64e3a661b1692777197afc2ff7bca\">recurrent</span> infections.</p>",
