    {
      "text": "Which nerve is accountable for causing ear pain following a tonsillectomy procedure among the options provided?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Glossopharyngeal nerve"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Facial nerve"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Trigeminal nerve"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Vagus nerve"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: A) <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"13b0890d441692777188afdcb41e75\">Glossopharyngeal</span> nerve</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Glossopharyngeal nerve:</strong> The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"13b0890d441692777188afdcb41e75\">glossopharyngeal</span> nerve (cranial nerve IX) provides <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"408bcde7f01692777198acadb8e1c6\">sensory</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"45b8853be116927771901a9ff3eeb2\">innervation</span> to the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4356afe522169277719436b593e4b1\">oropharynx</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e670f25fb7169277720087be88cc56\">tonsillar</span> region. It also has <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"047f8930dd1692777197fed61e213c\">referred</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"408bcde7f01692777198acadb8e1c6\">sensory</span> pathways to the ear through its <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"391176370016927772011d1b8315bc\">tympanic</span> branch (Jacobson's nerve). This referral <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3aa5abc2fa169277719488e088076d\">pathway</span> explains the ear pain commonly experienced after a tonsillectomy.</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Facial nerve (Option B)</strong>: The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9fdd7489051692777202cffe3f24cc\">facial</span> nerve (cranial nerve VII) is primarily involved in motor <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"45b8853be116927771901a9ff3eeb2\">innervation</span> to the muscles of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9fdd7489051692777202cffe3f24cc\">facial</span> expression and does not provide <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"408bcde7f01692777198acadb8e1c6\">sensory</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"45b8853be116927771901a9ff3eeb2\">innervation</span> to the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e670f25fb7169277720087be88cc56\">tonsillar</span> or pharyngeal region.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Trigeminal nerve (Option C)</strong>: The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6d1eb38ecf1692777200bb65bbdefb\">trigeminal</span> nerve (cranial nerve V) provides <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"408bcde7f01692777198acadb8e1c6\">sensory</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"45b8853be116927771901a9ff3eeb2\">innervation</span> to the face, including the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b9a0fc0e19169277718759be7a9732\">external ear</span> via its <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c2c10e783c1692777182a1d84457f9\">auriculotemporal</span> branch, but it is not directly involved in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e670f25fb7169277720087be88cc56\">tonsillar</span> pain.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Vagus nerve (Option D)</strong>: The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c8da04ed171692777201da65246acd\">vagus</span> nerve (cranial nerve X) provides <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"408bcde7f01692777198acadb8e1c6\">sensory</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"45b8853be116927771901a9ff3eeb2\">innervation</span> to parts of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"80452d1746169277719165b097dc7a\">larynx</span> and pharynx, but it is less commonly associated with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"047f8930dd1692777197fed61e213c\">referred</span> ear pain in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"68899ab3a11692777200d8823b50d8\">tonsillectomy</span> cases.</p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
