    {
      "text": "Dohlman’s procedure is for:",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Meckel’s diverticulum"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Zenker’s diverticulum"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Bochadlek hernia"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Menetrier’s disease"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: B) Zenker’s diverticulum</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Dohlman’s procedure</strong> is a <strong>minimally <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1c5272ad3d1692777190e71409d07a\">invasive</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"35ca8c2d5f16927771879351e8f97e\">endoscopic</span> technique</strong> used to treat <strong>Zenker’s diverticulum</strong>, a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0d9ab8e31b169277719584687d421a\">pharyngoesophageal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fba459ae6d1692777196f4374e9ac1\">pouch</span> that forms due to <strong>cricopharyngeal muscle dysfunction</strong>.</li>\n\t<li>The procedure involves <strong>endoscopic diverticulotomy</strong>, which <strong>divides the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"07bb7766221692777185a58cad9233\">cricopharyngeal</span> bar</strong>, allowing food to pass freely into the esophagus.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Zenker’s <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d12c5027f91692777186803150d054\">Diverticulum</span> & Dohlman’s Procedure</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Feature</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Description</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Definition</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Outpouching of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31ae8f4dc51692777193069d92be37\">mucosa</span> through Killian’s dehiscence</strong> (weak area in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a5c6cb079d16927771967e62ffee72\">posterior</span> pharynx)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Cause</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Cricopharyngeal dysfunction</strong> leading to high pressure and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d12c5027f91692777186803150d054\">diverticulum</span> formation</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Symptoms</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>1. <strong>Dysphagia</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>2. <strong>Regurgitation of undigested food</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>3. <strong>Halitosis</strong> (bad breath)</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>4. <strong>Aspiration pneumonia</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Diagnosis</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Barium swallow X-ray</strong> (shows a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a5c6cb079d16927771967e62ffee72\">posterior</span> pharyngeal pouch)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Treatment</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Dohlman’s procedure (endoscopic diverticulotomy)</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Open surgery if large</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<figure class=\"caption_element\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"NA\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"NA\" data-source=\"NA\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"592\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/PnqvSlLqrVG2lPfu08nl1746705292.png\" width=\"940\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n<p><strong>Incorrect Options:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Meckel’s <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d12c5027f91692777186803150d054\">diverticulum</span> (Option A):</strong> is incorrect because <strong>Meckel’s <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d12c5027f91692777186803150d054\">diverticulum</span> is a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"488a4efe7d16927771840c9e29f164\">congenital</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bead1cecfa16927771979940742ada\">remnant</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4df1564f3c1692777202da97b54e7e\">vitelline</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6198b5f22b16927771867e4ef8108f\">duct</span> in the small intestine</strong> and is managed surgically by <strong>Meckel’s diverticulectomy</strong>, not Dohlman’s procedure.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Bochdalek <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9cf1b2a8bc16927771899480554f5a\">hernia</span> (Option C):</strong> is incorrect because <strong>Bochdalek <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9cf1b2a8bc16927771899480554f5a\">hernia</span> is a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"488a4efe7d16927771840c9e29f164\">congenital</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"06ff18f51216927771867fe1461a04\">diaphragmatic</span> hernia</strong> due to <strong>failure of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8f7c89df6e16927771951d19c26422\">pleuroperitoneal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"34cd707428169277719272942b7905\">membrane</span> to close</strong> and is repaired via <strong>surgical <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2b4569285f1692777184282b1ca3f1\">closure</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5b42867b61169277718692205c2447\">diaphragm</span> defect</strong>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Menetrier’s disease (Option D):</strong> is incorrect because <strong>Menetrier’s disease is a rare <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\">gastric</span> hypertrophic condition</strong> with <strong>protein loss and increased <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ab75ea330616927771938a64f8ebd6\">mucus</span> secretion</strong>, treated with <strong>medical therapy or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"60e93bf2cd169277718880e1f2920b\">gastrectomy</span> in severe cases</strong>, not Dohlman’s procedure.</p>",
