        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer C- Tracheostomy</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>A <strong>tracheostomy</strong> is a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> procedure where an opening is created in the neck, directly into the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9ebd78bd471692777200ede69e8ed1\">trachea</span> (windpipe), to provide an <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3b9dd3166f1692777180b697887ccb\">airway</span> and to allow for breathing when the upper <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3b9dd3166f1692777180b697887ccb\">airway</span> is blocked or compromised.</li>\n\t<li>This is usually performed in cases of long-term <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b45075a0e1169277719252465ca5ba\">mechanical ventilation</span> needs, upper <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3b9dd3166f1692777180b697887ccb\">airway</span> obstruction, or trauma to the neck.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Tracheostomy</strong>:</p>\n\n<table align=\"center\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Aspect</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Details</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td rowspan=\"3\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Indications</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Upper <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3b9dd3166f1692777180b697887ccb\">airway</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"39f44b27bf169277719416f29a74ee\">obstruction</span> (tumors, foreign body)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Prolonged mechanical ventilation</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Neurological conditions (e.g., <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d816ba952f1692777199fc69bd7c56\">spinal</span> cord injury)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Procedure</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Incision made below vocal cords, tube inserted into trachea.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Tube Types</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Cuffed:</strong> for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a58f1f33f81692777201ad5e0d60ca\">ventilation</span> support.</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Uncuffed:</strong> for stable <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3b9dd3166f1692777180b697887ccb\">airway</span> or weaning.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Complications</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Infection, bleeding, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c739a6fb2b1692777200e2ada8023c\">tracheal</span> stenosis, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fb7ff97e071692777180252299cf10\">accidental</span> dislodgement, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1788e0d4301692777199d457616bd4\">swallowing</span> difficulty.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Care</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Regular cleaning, monitoring for infection, and tube changes.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Advantages</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Comfortable for long-term ventilation, lower risk of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3b9dd3166f1692777180b697887ccb\">airway</span> damage compared to intubation.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"National Heart Lung and Blood Institute (NIH)\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"Open access\" data-source=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tracheotomy#/media/File:Tracheostomy_NIH.jpg\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"423\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/qf571g5aeFjq1BkK2z041747122204.png\" width=\"780\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>\n\n<p><strong>Incorrect Options:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Endotracheal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"83e66fab2f1692777190a43a6e300f\">intubation</span> (Option A):</strong> is incorrect because it involves the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c88a7c1a0116927771909b2463968d\">insertion</span> of a tube into the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9ebd78bd471692777200ede69e8ed1\">trachea</span> via the mouth or nose, not through a neck incision.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Needle <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d2448812171692777185adac472e7e\">cricothyroidotomy</span> (Option B):</strong> is incorrect because this emergency procedure involves inserting a needle through the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ebe088dd1e1692777185885b701072\">cricothyroid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"34cd707428169277719272942b7905\">membrane</span> in the neck to secure an <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3b9dd3166f1692777180b697887ccb\">airway</span> in life-threatening situations, but does not involve creating a permanent opening as in a tracheostomy.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Oropharyngeal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3b9dd3166f1692777180b697887ccb\">airway</span> (Option D):</strong> is incorrect because this is a device inserted into the mouth to maintain an open airway, typically in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6d87fbc02c16927772014ec4cead53\">unconscious</span> patients, and does not involve a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2afbd932801692777190be690704b3\">incision</span> or permanent <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3b9dd3166f1692777180b697887ccb\">airway</span> opening.</p>",
