    {
      "text": "A female homemaker arrives with symptoms of nasal congestion, reduced sense of smell, and a dry discharge from the nose that is greenish and crusty. Upon examination, the nasal passages appear spacious, and the turbinates are found to be shriveled. Which surgical procedure would be suitable for this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Submucous resection"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Young’s operation"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Septoplasty"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Vidian neurectomy"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer B- Young's operation</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t<p><strong>Young's operation</strong> is a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> procedure used to treat <strong>atrophic rhinitis</strong> (also known as \"ozena\"), which is characterized by <strong>dryness of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31c5d0e75f16927771938d8e2daa4c\">nasal</span> mucosa</strong>, <strong>crusting</strong>, and sometimes <strong>foul-smelling discharge</strong>.</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p>This condition can cause <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31c5d0e75f16927771938d8e2daa4c\">nasal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2dd9736fdf16927771849f5a925f7d\">congestion</span> and a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"10c83adb331692777197f775bec1aa\">reduced</span> sense of smell, which aligns with the symptoms described in this patient.</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p>Young’s operation involves removing the affected <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31ae8f4dc51692777193069d92be37\">mucosa</span> and sometimes involves creating a more functional <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31c5d0e75f16927771938d8e2daa4c\">nasal</span> environment.</p>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Young’s Operation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t<p><strong>Indication</strong>: Young’s operation is commonly used in cases of <strong>atrophic rhinitis</strong> where there is dry, crusty <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9dd87431ba1692777186ecfb21d258\">discharge</span> from the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31c5d0e75f16927771938d8e2daa4c\">nasal</span> passages along with a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"10c83adb331692777197f775bec1aa\">reduced</span> sense of smell and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31c5d0e75f16927771938d8e2daa4c\">nasal</span> obstruction.</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p><strong>Procedure</strong>: The surgery typically involves removing the affected, atrophic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31ae8f4dc51692777193069d92be37\">mucosa</span> and possibly re-establishing the function of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31c5d0e75f16927771938d8e2daa4c\">nasal</span> passages to improve breathing and reduce symptoms like dryness and crusting.</p>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Incorrect Options:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Submucous <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"17b5bd50d91692777197ea9cb7f468\">resection</span> (Option A)</strong>: is incorrect because it is performed to treat <strong>nasal septal deviation</strong>, not for conditions with excessive dryness or crusting, such as atrophic rhinitis.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Vidian <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c51a7900171692777193f745b9d65f\">neurectomy</span> (Option D)</strong>: is incorrect because Vidian <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c51a7900171692777193f745b9d65f\">neurectomy</span> is used to reduce excessive <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31c5d0e75f16927771938d8e2daa4c\">nasal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9b0ae3750916927771986c15d4ff4d\">secretion</span> in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"10322d88e516927771846e0a64000c\">chronic rhinitis</span> or other conditions with excessive <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"31c5d0e75f16927771938d8e2daa4c\">nasal</span> discharge, but not for atrophic rhinitis.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Septoplasty (Option C)</strong>: is incorrect as it is performed for <strong>nasal septal deviation</strong> to correct airflow, but the patient in question is dealing with dryness and crusting, rather than a structural issue like septal deviation.</p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
