    {
      "text": "What surgery is being performed in the image shown?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Total ethmoidectomy"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Partial ethmoidectomy"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Total maxillectomy"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Partial maxillectomy"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Option C - Total maxillectomy</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>The <strong>Weber–Ferguson incision</strong> is a classical <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> approach for accessing the <strong>maxilla and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e23ca9914316927771948eba43a1e9\">paranasal</span> sinuses</strong>, providing wide exposure.</li>\n\t<li>The image shows an <strong>exposed maxillary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ddba4206eb169277718335596e86da\">cavity</span> with removal of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1ba6a9cfe11692777181950edd7a6d\">anterior</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"db46007ad21692777192dcc160a2e2\">medial</span> walls</strong>, which is characteristic of a <strong>total maxillectomy</strong>.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Total maxillectomy</strong> involves removal of the entire maxilla, including anterior, medial, posterior, and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"49c4ef5b9d1692777190c0277f8344\">inferior</span> walls, usually performed for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f8aaf091221692777191f73e810e94\">malignant</span> tumors of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"84514257721692777192f1748073bd\">maxilla</span> or advanced sinonasal malignancies.</li>\n\t<li>In the given scenario, the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> field and the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2afbd932801692777190be690704b3\">incision</span> markings confirm the diagnosis of <strong>total maxillectomy</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Incorrect Options:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Total <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e0ab3b392216927771874d31ffb169\">ethmoidectomy</span> (Option A):</strong> Complete removal of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"77d6d0146716927771877b0c93c24f\">ethmoid</span> air cells, done for extensive <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"77d6d0146716927771877b0c93c24f\">ethmoid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b0046463171692777198e0beea83e7\">sinus</span> disease, not for lesions requiring maxillary bone removal.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Partial <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e0ab3b392216927771874d31ffb169\">ethmoidectomy</span> (Option B):</strong> Involves selective removal of diseased <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"77d6d0146716927771877b0c93c24f\">ethmoid</span> cells while preserving healthy mucosa, unrelated to the maxillary walls.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Partial <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7e1612510d1692777192cfe698ecc1\">maxillectomy</span> (Option D):</strong> Involves removal of only part of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"84514257721692777192f1748073bd\">maxilla</span> (e.g., <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"db46007ad21692777192dcc160a2e2\">medial</span> wall in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"db46007ad21692777192dcc160a2e2\">medial</span> maxillectomy) while sparing other bony walls; in the image, multiple walls are removed indicating a total, not partial, procedure.</p>",
