    {
      "text": "A structure passing deep to the submandibular gland and curving around the inferior border of the mandible during submandibular gland excision surgery. Identify the structure labeled ‘X’ in the following image.",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Facial nerve"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Marginal mandibular nerve"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Facial artery"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Trigeminal nerve"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Option C - <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9fdd7489051692777202cffe3f24cc\">Facial</span> artery</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation: </strong></p>\n\n<p>The structure marked ‘X’ is identified as the <strong>facial artery.</strong></p>\n\n<p>In this image:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6dc33c9af116927771993596438eb2\">submandibular</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4744bb90c21692777188c8957f9faa\">gland</span> is clearly exposed.</li>\n\t<li>The vessel marked is coursing through or very close to the gland, which is a characteristic feature of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9fdd7489051692777202cffe3f24cc\">facial</span> artery.</li>\n\t<li>It needs to be <strong>ligated and divided during <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6dc33c9af116927771993596438eb2\">submandibular</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4744bb90c21692777188c8957f9faa\">gland</span> removal.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9fdd7489051692777202cffe3f24cc\">facial</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a66cd3adaa1692777182e77cb23021\">artery</span> is a key <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"116f86834a1692777181a914379270\">anatomical</span> landmark during <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6dc33c9af116927771993596438eb2\">submandibular</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4744bb90c21692777188c8957f9faa\">gland</span> excision. It typically runs deep to or within the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6dc33c9af116927771993596438eb2\">submandibular</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4744bb90c21692777188c8957f9faa\">gland</span> and is often seen as a prominent vessel in this <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> field. It originates from the<strong> external <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8593e48e0416927771834eaedb0bfd\">carotid</span> artery</strong>, passes deep to the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a5c6cb079d16927771967e62ffee72\">posterior</span> belly of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"25d67c73f516927771861326d5044c\">digastric</span> and stylohyoid, and then enters the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6dc33c9af116927771993596438eb2\">submandibular</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4744bb90c21692777188c8957f9faa\">gland</span> before <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5cd4f7994016927771911e5a8ab270\">looping</span> over the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55c062d44f16927771919375042b03\">mandible</span> to supply the face.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"\" data-source=\"\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"475\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/V0Nf3uZNtXdxReUU5lQR1755511567.png\" width=\"600\" /></p>\n\n<p><strong>Incorrect Options:</strong></p>\n\n<p>The <strong>facial nerve (Option A)</strong> does not run through the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6dc33c9af116927771993596438eb2\">submandibular</span> region. It enters the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"42d0553c3916927771944110a6f15b\">parotid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4744bb90c21692777188c8957f9faa\">gland</span> and branches within it.</p>\n\n<p>Th<strong>e marginal mandibular nerve (Option B) </strong>is closely related to the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6dc33c9af116927771993596438eb2\">submandibular</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4744bb90c21692777188c8957f9faa\">gland</span> and is at risk during surgery, it is a thin, delicate nerve running <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ebb480187d1692777199e233e9e356\">superficial</span> to the gland, not a thick, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a2af1612021692777196c7044ee75b\">pulsatile</span> structure like in the image.</p>\n\n<p>The <strong>trigeminal nerve (Option D)</strong> and its major branches are not present in this <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> plane. It does not pass through or near the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6dc33c9af116927771993596438eb2\">submandibular</span> gland.</p>",
